FBIS3-38936 "drweu027aa_94008" FBIS-WEU-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Canada Still Opposed to Air Strikes in Bosnia LD0802152294 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 1430 GMT 8 Feb 94 LD0802152294 Montreal Radio Canada International Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Defense Minister David Collenette says that despite the horror of the mortar attack on Sarajevo the Canadian Government is still opposed to air strikes. [Begin Collenette recording] We haven't changed our position since the prime minister announced it last month, which was that we believe that air strikes were not the way to deal with the problem at this time, until all other courses of action fail. As Mr. Ouellet said yesterday, we still believe that a negotiated settlement can be arrived at. [end recording] Defense Minister David Collenette: A primary consideration for Ottawa is the safety of Canada's 2,400 peacekeepers in former Yugoslavia.
